titleStmt.title: Deaths tryumph dash'd: or, An elegy on that faithful servant of God Master James Janeway, minister of the Gospel, who resting from his most zealous and profitable labours, fell asleep in the Lord the 12th of this instant, March 1673/4.

notesStmt.note: Verse: "How! Janeway dead! spare, Lord! oh spare thy rod ..."
Reproduction of original in the British Library.
